description: Established, administered, and led the new Net-Centric SIGIN Innovations Lab (NC-SIL) and Maryland Analysis Center (MAC). title: Transportation Security Specialist
description: - Supervised and performed complex transportation vetting and analysis in an effort to identify possible threats to national security. - Supervised using products from transportation threat research derived from DHS Daily Operations Summary, TSA Operations Executive Summary, National Targeting Center Daily Report, NCTC Situational reports, Intelligence Community Threat Assessments, and FBI Intelligence. - Provide input into developing products for TSA Administrator's Daily Intelligence Briefing, Threat Stream Products, TSA SPOT reports, TSA Leadership Briefs, TSOC Operations Briefings, Executive Binders, and Leadership Folder. - Supervised intelligence and open source research & analysis using government and other databases to develop comprehensive understanding of potential threats to transportation and Homeland Security. Supervised or reviewed the production of high quality papers, presentations, and briefings in support of transportation security and Homeland security issues prior to dissemination. - Directed intelligence research using NCTC Online, M3, AMHS, Intellipedia, IShare, Worldwide Incident Tracking System (WITS), CIA Wire and DNI Open Source, Automated Targeting System-Passenger (ATS-P) and the Treasury Enforcement Communication System (TECS), CLEAR, and the Official Airline Guide (OAG) to perform research and analysis in a transportation or Homeland security context. Supervised the identification of gaps in information and taking action to obtain the proper intelligence and law enforcement information to support accurate security threat assessments. - Supervised watchlist matching and vetting of data. Analyzed vetting system-produced results for possible matches of passengers to individuals on terrorism watch lists. Researching and interpreting data, querying additional databases, both classified and unclassified, and resolving that information with vetting results data to determine the potential for a valid match. - Serve on Diversity Advisory Council

title: Secure Flight Analyst
description: - Analyzed vetting system-produced results for possible matches of passengers to individuals on terrorism watch lists. - Researched and interpreted data, queried additional databases (both classified and unclassified) and compared this information with vetting results data to determine the potential for a valid match using TECS, NCIC, CBP, TIDE, and Counter Terrorism(CI) Watch Log. - Took appropriate actions for invalid matches and refer valid matches to TSA Office of Intelligence (OI) analysts and the Terrorist Screening Center for further action. - OI Augmentee - Notified on-duty Secure Flight (SF) Vetting Operations, Secure Flight Senior Watch Officers and Supervisors of any significant threat activity or possible trends in data. - Identified gaps in information and took action to obtain the proper intelligence and law enforcement information to support accurate security threat assessments. - On a daily basis I have used a computer User Interface to produce analytically sound, oral, and written referral reports to describe the nature and significance of valid matches to terrorism watch lists. - Worked closely with the Secure Flight Customer Service Center and the Secure Flight Customer Support Agents to resolve individual cases of mismatches of passengers to terrorism watch-list matches.
